    </div>

    <p>Elderberry's immune-supporting properties come from its high concentration of anthocyanins — the dark purple pigments that give elderberries their characteristic color. These compounds have been shown to inhibit viral replication, enhance cytokine production (signaling molecules that coordinate immune response), and provide antioxidant protection against oxidative stress. A 2019 meta-analysis in <em>Complementary Therapies in Medicine</em> found that elderberry supplementation significantly reduced both the duration and severity of upper respiratory infections.</p>

