      <cite>Complementary Therapies in Medicine, 2019 — 4 RCTs, meta-analysis</cite>
    </div>

    <h3>A Note on Raw Elderberry Safety</h3>

    <p>It is critical to understand that raw elderberries, bark, and leaves contain cyanogenic glycosides — compounds that release cyanide when metabolized. These are toxic and should never be consumed raw. All commercially prepared elderberry gummies use cooked, processed elderberry extract or concentrate, which eliminates cyanogenic glycosides completely. This is not a risk with any product on this list, but it is the reason why parents should never attempt to make elderberry supplements at home from raw berries without proper preparation.</p>

